/*******************************************
zeroneg  set all the negative 
         intensities of 2D spectra to zero
**********************************************/


zeroneg		Set All the Negative Intensities of 2D Spectra to Zero (C)

   Syntax: 	zeroneg

   Description:	"zeroneg" is used for the projection of proton 2D J-spectra 
   		at 45 degree to strip a high resolution proton spectrum down 
   		to a list of chemical shifts. The command "zeroneg" simply 
   		sets all negative intensities to zero.  
	
   Examples:	zeroneg
   		
   Related: 	rotate
   		foldj

